# ── Build output ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Derivatives are built in CI and deployed from there. They never
# enter git: GitHub Pages caps repos around 1 GB and history is
# permanent, so a committed derivative is a permanent cost.
_site/
.cache/
.eleventy-cache/


# ── THE AIRLOCK ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Originals live here and NEVER enter git history. SD-card dumps,
# Photos.app exports, RAW files, anything not yet stripped and
# verified. Only the output of `crustyimg ingest` — stripped,
# resized, verified — is ever committed, and it lands in
# src/posts/<slug>/, not here.
#
# One GPS-bearing file committed once is public forever. This is
# the single most important block in this file.
_incoming/
_originals/


# ── Belt and braces: formats that should never be committed ───
# src/posts/<slug>/ holds only stripped web JPEG/PNG/WebP/AVIF.
# If a RAW file or a HEIC straight off a phone ever ends up staged,
# it means the airlock was bypassed — so refuse them globally.
# HEIC in particular carries GPS by default and browsers can't
# display it anyway; it has no business in the repo.
*.heic
*.HEIC
*.heif
*.HEIF
*.raf
*.RAF
*.nef
*.NEF
*.dng
*.DNG
*.cr2
*.CR2
*.cr3
*.CR3
*.arw
*.ARW
*.orf
*.ORF
*.rw2
*.RW2
*.tif
*.tiff
*.psd
*.xmp


# ── Node ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
.npm/
*.tsbuildinfo


# ── Environment / secrets ─────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example


# ── macOS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes


# ── Editors ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo


# ── Rust / crustyimg, if it ever lands in-tree ────────────────
target/


# ── Local scratch · download staging, not part of the site ────
# Files were downloaded here and copied into place; keep the staging
# area and any download archives out of history.
tmp/
*.zip


# ── Internal working material · kept on disk, never published ──
# The build brief, the design/roadmap notes, the static design-reference
# render, and handoff archives live locally but stay out of this public,
# permanent history. Re-add deliberately (its own commit) if one should
# ever go public.
docs/background/
design_handoff/
design/
